= \rho \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} + \rho u \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} + u \left( \frac{\partial \rho}{\partial t} + \frac{\partial}{\partial x}(\rho u) \right) 

= \rho \left[ \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} + u \frac{\partial u}{\partial x} \right] 

= \rho \left[ \frac{\partial}{\partial t} + u \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \right] u 

= \frac{D}{Dt} \text{ (Material Derivative/ Substantive Derivative/ Total Derivative)} 

\frac{D}{Dt} = \frac{\partial}{\partial t} + u \frac{\partial}{\partial x}

\rho \frac{Du}{Dt} = -\frac{\partial p}{\partial x} + \frac{\partial \tau}{\partial y} 

\text{Newtonian fluid}\ \tau = \mu \frac{\partial u}{\partial y} 

\rho \frac{Du}{Dt} = -\frac{\partial p}{\partial x} + \mu \frac{\partial^2 u}{\partial y^2} \text{ (Navier-Stokes Equation 1D)}

\mu u(y) = \frac{dp}{dx}\frac{y^2}{2} + \left(\frac{\mu V}{\delta} - \frac{dp}{dx}\frac{\delta}{2}\right)y 
\begin{align*}
u(y) &= \frac{1}{2\mu}\frac{dp}{dx}\left(y^2 - \delta y\right) + \frac{V}{\delta}y \\
&= \frac{1}{2\mu}\left(-\frac{dp}{dx}\right)\left(\delta y - y^2\right) + \frac{V}{\delta}y \\
&= \frac{1}{2\mu}\left(-\frac{dp}{dx}\right)\delta^2\left[\frac{y}{\delta} - \left(\frac{y}{\delta}\right)^2\right] + \left(\frac{V}{\delta}\right)y \end{align*}
